Terra’s home!! She spent the last two days at the vet. Her uterus became infected and she grew what’s called a pile. I had to have her speyed immediately or she would have died…now before all you bleeding hearts offer up your reasons why I should’ve speyed her to begin with, I wanted to keep terra in my family for the kids. The only way I could do that was by having puppies. I’ve put this dog through so much trying to have puppies, and she has become so much work since my wife leaving me with two kids, that I actually considered putting her down…but then I thought about telling my kids that their terra wasn’t coming home from the vet’s…then who would keep the boogie man away when it was bedtime?! I love these kids, and I love this dog. I am truly a lucky man to have been blessed with such an awesome dog and two amazing children. Daddy loves you all!! 
.
.
.
.
.
.

So back in august ‘22 my ex wife decided to tell the DA that I locked her in a room. I spent the next 22hrs in central booking and when I was arraigned, the judge put a full stay away order on my (ex)wife, and my son. I would spend the next 3 or 4 months in and out of criminal court facing 21years in prison (three separate charges that each carried 7years). Now, still in family court where she is actively pursuing trying to keep me out of my children’s lives for good, this is the limited time I get to spend with them. I have missed one of each of their birthdays, Christmas with them, Easter, Valentine’s Day, st Patrick’s…and a whole bunch of other special occasions since. I did recently get to see my son step up from pre K to kindergarten, and got to have donuts with my little princess at day care. This is how I spent my Father’s Day with them…which is the last time I’ve seen them physically. As of now (until September), I’m allowed to see my kids 52 days out of the year. I try to make every minute count with them since they are limited…I don’t really have a closing statement here. Just wanted to share my story and my pics of them. I miss not seeing them on a daily basis, and not getting to raise them right now. It really hurts, and I’m getting tired of being patient. Daddy loves you John, and daddy loves you Kristen. See you again soon. 
.

.
.
